The library is not yet installed in the project. Here are the full API details from the official documentation.

---

## ResumableZoom API Reference

### Props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `style` | `ViewStyle` | `{ flex: 1 }` | Container styles; `justifyContent` and `alignItems` are enforced internally |
| `extendGestures` | `boolean` | `false` | Expands gesture detection area to the full component size |
| `minScale` | `number` | `1` | Minimum pinch scale (must be >= 1) |
| `maxScale` | `SizeVector<number> \| number` | `6` | Maximum pinch scale. Pass a number for a fixed max, or `{ width, height }` (the image's actual pixel resolution) to let the component calculate the max scale from the resolution |
| `panMode` | `'clamp' \| 'free' \| 'friction'` | `'clamp'` | Pan boundary behavior. `clamp` stops at edges, `free` allows unbounded movement, `friction` applies drag beyond edges |
| `scaleMode` | `'clamp' \| 'bounce'` | `'bounce'` | Scale boundary behavior. `bounce` rubber-bands past limits, `clamp` hard-stops |
| `allowPinchPanning` | `boolean` | `true` | Whether panning is allowed during a pinch gesture |
| `pinchMode` | `'clamp' \| 'free'` | `'clamp'` | Pinch boundary behavior (only effective when `allowPinchPanning: true`) |
| `decay` | `boolean` | `true` | Apply decay (momentum) animation when pan gesture ends |
| `panEnabled` | `boolean` | `true` | Enable/disable pan and swipe gestures |
| `pinchEnabled` | `boolean` | `true` | Enable/disable pinch gesture |
| `tapsEnabled` | `boolean` | `true` | Enable/disable tap gestures (single tap, double tap) |
| `longPressDuration` | `number` | `500` | Milliseconds to trigger long press (> 250 recommended) |

### Callbacks

| Callback | Signature | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `onTap` | `(e: TapGestureEvent) => void` | Single tap |
| `onSwipe` | `(direction: 'up' \| 'down' \| 'left' \| 'right') => void` | Requires `panMode: 'clamp'` |
| `onPanStart` | `(e: PanGestureEvent) => void` | Pan begins |
| `onOverPanning` | `(x: number, y: number) => void` | **Worklet callback** -- runs on the UI thread. Fires when panning beyond content boundaries |
| `onPanEnd` | `(e: PanGestureEvent) => void` | Pan ends |
| `onPinchStart` | `(e: PinchGestureEvent) => void` | Pinch begins |
| `onPinchEnd` | `(e: PinchGestureEvent) => void` | Pinch ends |
| `onLongPress` | `(e: LongPressEvent) => void` | Long press detected |
| `onUpdate` | `(state: CommonZoomState<number>) => void` | **Worklet callback** -- fires on every transformation change (translate/scale) |
| `onGestureEnd` | `() => void` | Fires when all gestures and resulting animations have completed |

### Ref Type: `ResumableZoomRefType`

```typescript
const ref = useRef<ResumableZoomRefType>(null);
```

| Method | Signature | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `getState` | `() => CommonZoomState<number>` | Returns current transformation values |
| `getVisibleRect` | `() => Rect` | Returns `{ x, y, width, height }` of the currently visible area |
| `setTransformState` | `(state: CommonTransformState<number>, animate?: boolean) => void` | Applies a transformation. `animate` defaults to `true` |
| `reset` | `(animate?: boolean) => void` | Resets to initial state. `animate` defaults to `true` |
| `zoom` | `(newScale: number, position?: Vector<number>) => void` | Programmatic zoom to `newScale` centered at `position` (defaults to center of component) |

### Key Types

**`CommonZoomState<number>`**
```typescript
{
  containerSize: { width: number; height: number };
  childSize: { width: number; height: number };
  maxScale: number;
  translateX: number;
  translateY: number;
  scale: number;
}
```

**`CommonTransformState<number>`**
```typescript
{
  translateX: number;
  translateY: number;
  scale: number;
}
```

**`Rect`**
```typescript
{ x: number; y: number; width: number; height: number }
```

### Usage Pattern

```tsx
import { ResumableZoom, type ResumableZoomRefType } from 'react-native-zoom-toolkit';

const ref = useRef<ResumableZoomRefType>(null);

<ResumableZoom
  ref={ref}
  maxScale={{ width: 1920, height: 1080 }}  // pass actual image resolution
  panMode="clamp"
  onSwipe={(direction) => {
    if (direction === 'left' || direction === 'right') navigateToNextImage();
  }}
  onTap={() => toggleUI()}
  onUpdate={(state) => {
    'worklet';
    // runs on UI thread, use for animated value updates
  }}
>
  <Image source={{ uri }} style={size} />
</ResumableZoom>
```

**Key integration notes:**
- `maxScale` accepting `SizeVector<number>` (`{ width, height }`) is the preferred approach for images -- pass the actual pixel dimensions and the component calculates the appropriate max zoom relative to the displayed size.
- `onOverPanning` and `onUpdate` are **worklet callbacks** (run on the Reanimated UI thread). Mark them with `'worklet'` directive or use `useWorkletCallback`.
- `onSwipe` only fires when `panMode` is `'clamp'` and the content is at scale 1 (not zoomed in).
- Double-tap to zoom is built in when `tapsEnabled` is true. It toggles between `minScale` and `maxScale`.

